Dear Tyler, I am a taco. I know there are a lot of other tacos in this 
world like me, but I hope you'll read this comment and listen to my story. 
I've been raised in Taco Bell, I've lived my whole life there. My childhood 
consisted of me watching my relatives be sold off into slavery and sold to 
people I didn't even know. We, the taco community, were always frightened. 
Scared that one day we would be ripped apart from our family, but one day I 
got the courage and said NO I will NOT be a victim NO MORE. So I put on my 
boots and went out of the Taco Bell. I was homeless for over 6 months, 
selling drugs to other tacos just to get by. Until one day God spoke to me, 
he told me; do not worry little taco for I am here for you and I will
